</ol>
<p>None of this would be possible without the incredible work done by <span class="printuser avatarhover"><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/metaphysician" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1698079); return false;"><img class="small" src="http://www.wikidot.com/avatar.php?userid=1698079&amp;amp;size=small&amp;amp;timestamp=1603308106" alt="Metaphysician" style="background-image:url(http://www.wikidot.com/userkarma.php?u=1698079)" /></a><a href="http://www.wikidot.com/user:info/metaphysician" onclick="WIKIDOT.page.listeners.userInfo(1698079); return false;">Metaphysician</a></span> - {<a href="http://www.scp-wiki.wikidot.com/metaphysician">Author Page</a>}</p>
</blockquote>
<p>This canon represents months and months of work, planning, and execution.</p>
<h4><span>So you wanna write for In Memoria, Adytum?</span></h4>
<p>The thing to remember is that this is unabashedly Sarkic. It builds upon the Sarkic lore written by Metaphysician, but it doesn't include all of the things that gets tagged &quot;Sarkic&quot;. This isn't meant to be comedic or wholesome. Sure, that can exist here, but this (at it's very core) is a story about vengeance, retribution for thousands of years of suffering and death at the hands of those who thought they were &quot;better&quot;.</p>
<p>Each act is split by how aware the Foundation is of what is going on, and each act will be ended by both a titular tale and a final &quot;Imperator Mundi&quot; thing.</p>
<p>The &quot;Assistentes&quot; section is specifically for things that aren't part of the primary story arc, but exists within the canon itself. Please feel free to reach out to me if you'd like to storyboard stuff to add.</p>
<p><a href="http://scp-wiki.wikidot.com/theme:memoria">There is also a theme, if you wish</a></p>
